        <member name="T:DAL.Contracts.IUnitOfWork">
            <summary>
            Defines a transactional scope that shares a single database connection across multiple repositories.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            <para>
            Obtain a new instance from <see cref="M:DAL.Factory.DalFactory.CreateUnitOfWork"/>.
            The intended usage pattern is:
            <code>
            using (var uow = DalFactory.CreateUnitOfWork())
            {
                uow.BeginTransaction();
                // use uow.*Repository to perform coordinated writes
                uow.Commit();
            }
            </code>
            </para>
            <para>
            If <see cref="M:DAL.Contracts.IUnitOfWork.Commit"/> is never called, <see cref="M:System.IDisposable.Dispose"/> will automatically
            roll back any open transaction when the <c>using</c> block exits.
            </para>
            </remarks>
        </member>
