        <member name="T:DAL.Impl.BaseBusinessSqlRepository">
            <summary>
            Base class for all business-domain SQL repositories.
            Extends <see cref="T:Service.Impl.BaseRepository"/> with support for shared <see cref="T:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection"/>
            and <see cref="T:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlTransaction"/> injection by <see cref="T:DAL.Impl.SqlServer.UnitOfWork"/>.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            When <see cref="P:DAL.Impl.BaseBusinessSqlRepository.CurrentConnection"/> is set (i.e., the repository is enrolled in a UoW
            transaction), the shadowed helper methods use the shared connection/transaction instead of
            opening a new one. When not enrolled, they fall back to the base class behaviour.
            </remarks>
        </member>
